# âš¡ Install Kind (Kubernetes in Docker)  

**Kind** is a tool for running local Kubernetes clusters using Docker. This guide provides installation commands for different architectures.

---

## ğŸ“¥ **Installation Steps**  

### ğŸ–¥ï¸ **For AMD64 / x86_64**  
```bash
[ "$(uname -m)" = "x86_64" ] && curl -Lo ./kind https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/dl/v0.27.0/kind-linux-amd64
```

### ğŸ“± **For ARM64**  
```bash
[ "$(uname -m)" = "aarch64" ] && curl -Lo ./kind https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/dl/v0.27.0/kind-linux-arm64
```

### ğŸš€ **Make Kind Executable & Move to System Path**  
```bash
chmod +x ./kind
sudo mv ./kind /usr/local/bin/kind
```

